title: Space Force is creating its own culture but will be ‘tightly coupled’ to the Air Force
summary: The Space Force is a separate U.S. military branch but will have to stay “tightly coupled” to the Air Force in order to be successful, Air Force Secretary Frank Kendall said Jan. 19.

title: One Year into the Biden Administration, NASA Looks to Future
summary: Over the past year, NASA has made valuable contributions to Biden-Harris Administration’s goals – leading on the global stage, addressing the urgent issue of climate change, creating high paying jobs, and inspiring future generations.

title: Space and national security: What to expect in 2022
summary: The Space Force stands on firmer political ground but is coming under pressure to deliver new technologies to counter threats from Russia and China. The Space Development Agency is counting down to the launch of its first operational satellites. And ULA is still waiting for Blue Origin to deliver engines for Vulcan’s maiden flight.

title: Radian Aerospace raises seed round to fund work on spaceplane
summary: A startup has raised a seed round of funding to pursue development of what’s long been considered the holy grail of space transportation: a single-stage-to-orbit reusable spaceplane.

title: Cosmonauts complete Russian spacewalk to integrate Prichal node
summary: Two Russian cosmonauts have conducted a spacewalk at the International Space Station (ISS) to fully configure and integrate the outpost’s newest module to support future operations.

title: Satellogic raises $150 million from fund led by former treasury secretary
summary: A fund led by Steven Mnuchin, former treasury secretary, will invest $150 million into Earth imaging company Satellogic, helping close a delayed merger with a special purpose acquisition corporation (SPAC).

title: SpaceX launches 2,000th Starlink satellite
summary: A package of 49 Starlink satellites that rode a Falcon 9 rocket into orbit Tuesday night from Florida included the 2,000th spacecraft to launch into SpaceX’s broadband internet network.

title: Federal budget stalemate having ‘ripple effects’ on national security space missions
summary: If a CR continues, two national security space missions funded in 2022 would have to be pushed into 2023 or beyond.
